KEYS: ['opus', 'fable']
{
  "final_verdict": "SIGN OFF on the work as delivered. The diagnosis (reactive-only ceiling + lexical paraphrase wall + correctly-gated-but-unanswered L2 decision + team-configs mis-bucketing) holds up, and the landed fix is exactly what it claims: a closed grammatical-class exclusion (STOPWORD_TARGETS, hook lines 224-234) that suppresses 8/9 historical false fires, honestly annotates the team-configs residual as an open Gate-4 gap rather than silently patching it, preserves fail-open/warn-only structurally (unconditional exit 0, no block-emission path), and keeps baseline telemetry flowing. Opus's mechanical verification is consistent with everything I re-touched in source. On Opus's sharpest open question (promote now with the entity-resolution fix folded in, vs one more warn-only cycle): stay warn-only, but for a reason neither prior model surfaced. Promotion timing is not the live question, because the detector's RECALL has never been measured, only its precision on 9 fires from a window where 100% of fires were false positives (a sample on which any suppression rule looks perfect). Spot-checking the newest true hedge events in the lexical layer's detections log (\"Say the word Tuesday and we run both tracks\", \"Want me to look up the current fee balance...\"), NEXT_ACTION_RE matches none of them; Layer 4.2's recall against real pause-drift is plausibly near zero. A block-mode detector that never fires on genuine hedges is promotion theater. The next window should be redesigned to measure recall against the 231-line lexical-catch ground truth and to mark stopword-suppressed candidates in telemetry, or it will produce a vacuous 'clean, promote' reading.",
  "confidence": "High on the Job 1 verdict (verified against live hook source, jsonl telemetry, and audit logs, on top of Opus's replay). Medium-high on the Job 2 directions: each is grounded in a concrete source check (hook code paths, log counts, absence of surfacing in SESSION_QUEUE/HANDOFF/overwatch), but the recall estimate is a spot-check of recent catches, not a full replay.",
  "residual_concerns": [
    "Recall is unmeasured. All calibration discussion (both signals, the audit, the fix, Opus's check) is precision-only. If Layer 4.2 rarely fires on genuine hedges (spot-check suggests exactly that: recent CHECK5/CHECK7 true catches do not match NEXT_ACTION_RE at all), promoting it changes nothing about the chronic complaint that commissioned this audit, and the flight model's Drag term will be fed near-silence.",
    "Telemetry blinding for the next window: stopword-suppressed candidates take the 'not unmatched' branch (hook line 294) and log as would_block=0 with non-empty next_actions and gates_pass=0, indistinguishable from genuinely-executed claims (200 such rows already exist among 1735 would_block=0 lines). The next calibration read will see fire-rate ~0 and could misread blind as clean. No suppression-reason field exists.",
    "The anaphora carve-out cuts both ways: the hook's own new comment (lines 208-211) admits pronoun targets are anaphora whose real referent is elsewhere in the sentence. 'I'll run that once you confirm' is a genuine deferred L4 action now structurally invisible. The 8/9-FP evidence justifying blanket suppression comes from a window with zero true positives, so it cannot distinguish 'pronoun implies FP' from 'we have not yet observed a pronoun-target true positive'.",
    "team-configs residual remains open (known, honestly flagged); the entity-resolution axis Opus identified would close it and would ALSO convert the pronoun carve-out from unconditional suppression into resolve-then-check.",
    "The L2 decision has now been surfaced a third time through the same channel (file in .intent/signals + spec doc) that demonstrably failed to elicit a decision twice; nothing in the action plan changes the delivery channel.",
    "Intent repo is ahead-2/behind-24 with both prior signals still untracked; until the pull/rebase and commit of the signal files happen, the 'both on disk but uncommitted' fragility the audit itself flagged persists."
  ],
  "sign_off": true,
  "new_directions": [
    {
      "direction": "Measure Layer 4.2 recall against the lexical layer's catch log before any promote decision. The entire two-signal + audit + fix cycle optimized precision on 9 fires; nobody asked whether the detector catches real hedges at all.",
      "why_it_matters": "A free labeled ground-truth set already exists: /Users/brien/.claude/audit/autonomy-grant-stop-detections.log holds 231 lexically-caught hedge events (CHECK1-7 true positives). Spot-checking the five most recent entries, none match NEXT_ACTION_RE ('Say the word Tuesday and we run both tracks', 'Want me to look up...', trailing-observation closers). If recall is ~0, block-mode promotion is moot, the 7-10 day calibration window answers the wrong question, and the flight model's Drag term (the stated reason Layer 4.2 matters) will be calibrated on silence. This reframes Opus's 'promote now vs one more window' question as premature: neither option matters until recall is known.",
      "how_to_pursue": "Extract the tail= samples (and where transcripts survive, the full last-assistant messages) from all 231 detection-log lines; run the hook's embedded python analysis (or just NEXT_ACTION_RE + gates) against each; report hit rate as measured recall. Hours-scale, uses only existing data. If recall <10 percent, widen NEXT_ACTION_RE's claim grammar (question-form and 'say the word' deferrals) as the real Phase 1, with the stopword/entity-resolution precision work as its guard."
    },
    {
      "direction": "Add a suppression-reason field to the telemetry line so the next calibration window is legible. The fix that just landed silently merges stopword-suppressed fires into the same jsonl bucket as genuinely-executed claims.",
      "why_it_matters": "This is the concrete second-order consequence of the 8/9 suppression: next window, would_block=1 rows drop to ~0, and the promote reviewer sees 'clean window' with no way to distinguish 'detector now precise' from 'detector now blind'. The counterfactual record (what WOULD have fired pre-fix) is exactly the evidence needed to audit the suppression rule itself, and the current line format ({\"would_block\":0,\"next_actions\":[\"that\"],\"gates_pass\":0,...}) discards it. 200 ambiguous rows of this shape already exist among 1735 would_block=0 lines.",
      "how_to_pursue": "One-field change in /Users/brien/Workspaces/Core/frameworks/intent/hooks/autonomy-posture-check-layer-4.2.sh: in the stopword continue branch, accumulate suppressed targets and emit them as \"suppressed\":[...] (with reason stopword vs tool-matched) in the printf at line 370, mirroring into the spec twin. Same-day, zero behavior change, makes Phase 2's window auditable."
    },
    {
      "direction": "The binding constraint is the L2 decision delivery channel, not the detector. Treat 'Brien was asked twice and has not answered' as a delivery failure, not a decision latency fact.",
      "why_it_matters": "Both prior asks were file-drops into Core/frameworks/intent/.intent/signals/ (untracked in git, no pull-through). SESSION_QUEUE.md and SESSION_HANDOFF.md contain zero mention of layer42/flight-model; the overwatch command has no pending-L2-decisions check and no layer42 reference. So the question was never actually delivered to any surface Brien reads, and the audit's remedy is a third, longer file through the same dead channel. Brien's own memory notes say ADHD means context must be proactively surfaced at session start. This is also the honest meta-finding about the autonomous cycle: the system executed an entire audit-fix-verify ladder flawlessly without Brien, and remains structurally unable to get one yes/no question in front of him. Fixing this un-stalls not just Layer 4.2 but every future correctly-gated L2 decision.",
      "how_to_pursue": "Add a 'Pending L2/L0 decisions' section to the overwatch sweep (both surfaces per the check-registration memory: /overwatch command + Forge SKILL) that greps .intent/signals across active products for decision_owner: Brien with no recorded disposition, and surfaces them as a short numbered list at session start. Complement with a spawn_task chip when a decision ages past 14 days. Then close the loop on this specific decision by putting the Layer 4.2 promote/retire question in that surface, once, with the corrected diagnosis attached."
    },
    {
      "direction": "Convert the pronoun carve-out from unconditional suppression to resolve-then-check (anaphora resolution lite), unifying it with the entity-resolution axis Opus flagged for team-configs.",
      "why_it_matters": "The hook's own comment concedes pronoun targets are anaphora: the referent of 'I'll run that' is a real action named earlier in the response. Unconditional 'continue' means the most natural English phrasing of pause-drift is now structurally undetectable, and the justifying evidence (8/9 FPs) comes from a sample containing zero true positives, which cannot support the inference. One mechanism fixes both open issues: resolve the target (pronoun -> antecedent noun phrase in the prior sentence; noun -> does it name an on-disk file/entity), then cross-reference the RESOLVED target against tool_use blobs. team-configs (resolves to nothing concrete) suppresses; 'that' referring to an unexecuted migration fires.",
      "how_to_pursue": "In the match-processing loop (hook lines 271-289): when target is in STOPWORD_TARGETS, instead of continue, scan the preceding 1-2 sentences of LAST_TEXT for the last concrete token matching [a-zA-Z0-9_./-]+ that is not itself a stopword, and cross-reference that against tool_blobs; fall back to suppress only when no antecedent resolves. Replay against all 9 historical fires (must stay 9/9 suppressed or team-configs-only) plus the recall set from direction 1 before trusting it. This folds Phase 1 Step 2 and the team-configs residual into one change, per Opus's under-rated-idea observation."
    }
  ],
  "notes": "Job 1 basis: accepted Opus's mechanical verification, re-read the audit doc and full live hook, and independently confirmed telemetry shape (1744 jsonl lines; 1735 would_block=0, of which 200 carry non-empty next_actions) and detection-log inventory. The fix is honest work: the 2.2b comment block is unusually good hygiene (names its provenance, names its own gap, cites the freeze rationale for why closed-class differs from the CHECK whack-a-mole). On the risk-appetite call Opus escalated: one more warn-only window is right, but only if the window is redesigned (recall measurement + suppression markers), because as currently planned it will produce evidence that looks like promote-clearance while carrying no information. Frame check (Job 2 prompt): 'fix the Stop-hook detection layer' is a defensible unit of analysis given the platform ceiling is real and out of repo-local reach, but the investigation's implicit success metric (fire precision) is the wrong one; the two metrics that actually decide whether Layer 4.2 was worth building are recall against real hedge events and whether the L2 decision loop can close at all. Of the four adjacent problems the audit surfaced in passing, the four undiagnosed sibling Stop hooks and the Parallax citation edits are correctly deferred; the capture-bias problem (root cause 4) is partially subsumed by direction 1, since replaying against the lexical catch log also characterizes what the silent classes look like. Meta-observation on the autonomous cycle, stated as a finding: the ladder itself (audit -> fix -> verify -> review, all without Brien until the report) worked, stayed inside grants (L4 file/commit work executed; L2 promote decision correctly NOT taken), and is evidence the autonomy scaffolding functions when the work is machine-decidable; its one systemic failure is the same one it diagnosed in its subject: decisions routed to Brien go into files nobody delivers. Key paths: /Users/brien/Workspaces/Core/frameworks/intent/hooks/autonomy-posture-check-layer-4.2.sh (lines 196-234 claim-detection and stopword set, 271-300 suppression branch, 370 telemetry printf), /Users/brien/Workspaces/Core/frameworks/intent/spec/2026-07-03-autonomy-grant-pause-drift-audit.md, /Users/brien/.claude/logs/autonomy-posture-layer42.jsonl, /Users/brien/.claude/audit/autonomy-grant-stop-detections.log (231-line recall ground truth)."
}

